{
  "page": "Wedding of Drogo and Daenerys Targaryen",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The title of this article is conjecture and may be subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sept13_Wedding_Feast_II.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f5/Sept13_Wedding_Feast_II.png/350px-Sept13_Wedding_Feast_II.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"240\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f5/Sept13_Wedding_Feast_II.png/525px-Sept13_Wedding_Feast_II.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f5/Sept13_Wedding_Feast_II.png/700px-Sept13_Wedding_Feast_II.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sept13_Wedding_Feast_II.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Drogo\" title=\"Drogo\">Drogo</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> at their wedding feast, by Sept13 © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>wedding of Drogo and Daenerys Targaryen</b> occurs in <a href=\"/index.php/298_AC\" title=\"298 AC\">298&#160;AC</a> outside the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_City\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free City\">Free City</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Drogo\" title=\"Drogo\">Drogo</a>, a <i><a href=\"/index.php/Khal\" title=\"Khal\">khal</a></i> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki\" title=\"Dothraki\">Dothraki</a>, marries <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a>, the sister of <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys Targaryen\">Viserys Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Wedding\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Wedding</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Attendees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Attendees</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#From_Pentos\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">From Pentos</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Dothraki\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dothraki</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Other_guests\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Other guests</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Drogo_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys Targaryen\">Viserys Targaryen</a> and his sister <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys</a> have lived in exile in the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a> in the aftermath of <a href=\"/index.php/Robert%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Robert&#39;s Rebellion\">Robert's Rebellion</a>. While the exiles are staying with <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio Mopatis</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Magister\" title=\"Magister\">magister</a> negotiates a <a href=\"/index.php/Betrothal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Betrothal\">betrothal</a> between Daenerys and <a href=\"/index.php/Drogo\" title=\"Drogo\">Drogo</a>, the greatest <i><a href=\"/index.php/Khal\" title=\"Khal\">khal</a></i> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki_sea\" title=\"Dothraki sea\">Dothraki sea</a>. In return, Drogo will help Viserys recover the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Usurper\" title=\"Usurper\">Usurper</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Daenerys is to meet Drogo for the first time at a feast held at <a href=\"/index.php/Drogo%27s_manse\" title=\"Drogo&#39;s manse\">his manse</a>. Illyrio has the girl wear a <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a> gown of deep plum, gilded sandals, a tiara, <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">golden</a> bracelets crusted with <a href=\"/index.php/Amethyst\" title=\"Amethyst\">amethysts</a>, and a heavy golden torc emblazoned with <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyrian</a> <a href=\"/index.php/High_Valyrian\" title=\"High Valyrian\">glyphs</a>, to emphasize the fact that she is a princess.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Other notables in attendance for the meeting are Khal <a href=\"/index.php/Moro\" title=\"Moro\">Moro</a> and his son <a href=\"/index.php/Rhogoro\" title=\"Rhogoro\">Rhogoro</a>, the brother of the <a href=\"/index.php/Archon_of_Tyrosh\" title=\"Archon of Tyrosh\">Archon of Tyrosh</a>, and the exiled <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Viserys accepts Jorah's offer of <a href=\"/index.php/Sworn_sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sworn sword\">service</a> that night.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Drogo agrees to marry Daenerys, he allows the siblings to live in his manse while he joins his <i><a href=\"/index.php/Khalasar\" title=\"Khalasar\">khalasar</a></i> outside of Pentos.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The city's magisters double the <a href=\"/index.php/City_watch_(Pentos)\" title=\"City watch (Pentos)\">city guard</a> while the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki\" title=\"Dothraki\">Dothraki</a> are nearby.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Viserys, while willing to wed Daenerys to Drogo to achieve his goals, is resentful of having to give her up, and the night before the wedding tries to enter her room and claim her <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenhead\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maidenhead\">maidenhead</a>. Illyrio, however, has the foresight to post guards on her room and ensure the impetuous Viserys does not undo \"<a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio%27s_plans\" title=\"Illyrio&#39;s plans\">years of planning</a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Wedding\">Wedding</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Drogo_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Wedding\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Daenerys_Drogo_Illyrio_Her_Silver.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/71/Daenerys_Drogo_Illyrio_Her_Silver.jpg/350px-Daenerys_Drogo_Illyrio_Her_Silver.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/71/Daenerys_Drogo_Illyrio_Her_Silver.jpg/525px-Daenerys_Drogo_Illyrio_Her_Silver.jpg 1.5x, /images/7/71/Daenerys_Drogo_Illyrio_Her_Silver.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Daenerys_Drogo_Illyrio_Her_Silver.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Drogo presents his bride gift, a <a href=\"/index.php/Silver_mare\" title=\"Silver mare\">silver mare</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a>, by Amok ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wedding\">wedding</a> is held in a field outside of Pentos, with the ceremony beginning at dawn and continuing until dusk. Daenerys and Drogo are seated on a large earthen ramp raised among the grass palaces of the Dothraki guests. Seated below the couple in places of high honor are Drogo's <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodrider\" title=\"Bloodrider\">bloodriders</a> and Viserys, Illyrio, and Jorah, although Viserys is angered at having to sit below Daenerys. Daenerys wears wedding silks, and Viserys wears a tunic of black wool that depicts the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> in scarlet.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Food served during the feast include steaming joints of meat, thick black sausages, Dothraki blood pies, fruits, sweetgrass stews, and delicate pastries from the kitchens of Pentos. Viserys is angered when <a href=\"/index.php/Slave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slave\">slaves</a> offer each course first to Daenerys and Drogo. Daenerys, too afraid to eat, refuses each offering and instead sips <a href=\"/index.php/Honey\" title=\"Honey\">honeyed</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Drogo largely ignores Daenerys during the wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> He tosses <a href=\"/index.php/Bronze\" title=\"Bronze\">bronze</a> medallions to women who dance before him with <a href=\"/index.php/Drum\" title=\"Drum\">drums</a> playing in the background. Warriors start mating with the dancers, and one of the men is slain when two of the warriors fight with <i><a href=\"/index.php/Arakh\" title=\"Arakh\">arakhs</a></i> over the same woman. A dozen men die before the day is through.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When the sun starts to go down, Drogo halts the feasting so that Daenerys can receive her bride gifts. From her brother, Daenerys receives three <a href=\"/index.php/Handmaid\" title=\"Handmaid\">handmaids</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Irri\" title=\"Irri\">Irri</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Jhiqui\" title=\"Jhiqui\">Jhiqui</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Doreah\" title=\"Doreah\">Doreah</a>, though the bride believes the women were actually provided by Illyrio. Jorah gives Daenerys a small stack of books detailing the histories and songs of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>. Illyrio gives the bride a chest containing fine velvets and damasks and three petrified <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon eggs</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Shadow_Lands\" title=\"Shadow Lands\">Shadow Lands</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Haggo\" title=\"Haggo\">Haggo</a> gives Daenerys a leather whip with a <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a> handle, <a href=\"/index.php/Cohollo\" title=\"Cohollo\">Cohollo</a> an <i>arakh</i> chased in <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Qotho\" title=\"Qotho\">Qotho</a> a double-curved <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonbone\" title=\"Dragonbone\">dragonbone</a> bow, but the bride declines the weapons of the bloodriders out of Dothraki tradition and instead gives them to Drogo. Other Dothraki guests give Daenerys slippers, jewels, <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a> rings, medallion belts, painted vests, soft furs, <a href=\"/index.php/Sandsilk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sandsilk\">sandsilks</a>, and even a gown made from the skins of a thousand mice, which Illyrio assures Daenerys is very lucky. Daenerys also receives jars of scent, needles and feathers, and tiny bottle of purple glass. As his own gift to his bride, Drogo gives Daenerys a magnificent <a href=\"/index.php/Silver_mare\" title=\"Silver mare\">silver mare</a>, which the girl takes for a brief ride.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the sun has gone down, the bride and groom ride out into the fields, Daenerys on her new mare and Drogo on <a href=\"/index.php/Drogo%27s_stallion\" title=\"Drogo&#39;s stallion\">his stallion</a>, so that their marriage can be consummated. As a thirteen-year-old girl who had been abused by her brother for most of her life and had been given no say in the marriage, Daenerys is terrified of her bridegroom and expects to be raped. Despite his fierce reputation, however, Drogo proves to be a surprisingly considerate lover. Although he and Daenerys share no common language, he establishes that he understands the word \"no,\" then begins touching her gently, trying to arouse her. Drogo does not begin to have intercourse with her until Daenerys expresses her approval and initiates it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Drogo_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After the wedding, Drogo's <i>khalasar</i> departs Pentos for <a href=\"/index.php/Vaes_Dothrak\" title=\"Vaes Dothrak\">Vaes Dothrak</a> so that Daenerys can be presented to the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Dosh_khaleen\" title=\"Dosh khaleen\">dosh khaleen</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Illyrio invites Viserys to remain with him in Pentos, but Viserys insists upon accompanying Drogo to ensure the <i>khal</i> honors their alliance.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Drogo initially ignores Daenerys during the day, but every night, contrary to his behavior at the wedding's consummation, he couples with her roughly, uncaring of her bruises and sores from riding and ignoring her cries of pain, until Daenerys considers suicide. However, Daenerys has a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_dream\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragon dream\">dragon dream</a> that gives her new confidence and strength. Eventually, Daenerys initiates sex with Drogo, marking the beginning of a loving relationship between them. On the far end of the Dothraki sea, on her fourteenth nameday, Daenerys reveals that she is pregnant.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Attendees\">Attendees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Drogo_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Attendees\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"From_Pentos\">From Pentos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Drogo_and_Daenerys_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: From Pentos\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Vanessa_Cole.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/df/Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Vanessa_Cole.jpg/350px-Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Vanessa_Cole.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"481\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/df/Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Vanessa_Cole.jpg/525px-Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Vanessa_Cole.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/df/Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Vanessa_Cole.jpg/700px-Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Vanessa_Cole.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Daenerys_Targaryen_by_Vanessa_Cole.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> with one of the three <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_eggs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragon eggs\">dragon eggs</a> gifted to her by <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio Mopatis</a>, by Vanessa Cole ©</div></div></div>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> King <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys Targaryen\">Viserys III Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\"><img alt=\"Pentos.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/01/Pentos.svg/20px-Pentos.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/01/Pentos.svg/30px-Pentos.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/01/Pentos.svg/40px-Pentos.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Magister <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio Mopatis</a></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dothraki\">Dothraki</